        <h3>Topography</h3>
        Situated in southwest Ethiopia, the Gambela Region has borders with the Southern Nations, Nationalities, and Peoples Region (SNNPR) in the southeast, Oromia Region in the northeast, and South Sudan in the west. Gambela is the nation's capital. The Central Statistical Agency (2013) projected that the population of the Gambela Region was roughly 400,000 in 2017. The Region is divided into four administrative zones: the Agnewak Zone, the Nuwer Zone, the Mezhenger Zone, and the Etang Special Zone. There are thirteen Woredas in these four Zones. Five ethnic groups are regarded as indigenous in the region.</p>
