    <div class="religion">
      <p>
        <h3>Religion</h3>
        Traditional African Religions: Many people in Gambella also adhere to traditional African religions, which are characterized by beliefs in ancestral spirits, natural forces, and rituals aimed at maintaining harmony with the spirit world. These traditional beliefs vary among different ethnic groups in Gambella, with practices such as ancestor veneration, divination, and spirit possession being common. Traditional religious leaders, known as shamans or priests, play important roles in mediating between the human and spirit realms and providing spiritual guidance to their communities.

Other Minority Religions: In addition to Christianity, Islam, and traditional African religions, there are smaller communities in Gambella that adhere to other faiths, such as Protestant Christianity, Catholicism, and indigenous belief systems unique to specific ethnic groups. These minority religious communities contribute to the religious diversity and pluralism of the region. </div>
